Subject: Diesel as a fuel treatment

Somebody posted this as a possible alternative this morning, here's what a 
friend wrote back to me:

> >A friend of a friend of a friend (in Australia) says gas
> >treatments are simply diesel fuel with some aromatics thrown
> >in. Any comments or knowledge on the topic in VV land?
> > Says you can toss a couple liters of diesel in vs. the gas
> > treatment and gain the same benefits. Would this be safe in
> >an modern car? I envision losing injectors and oxygen
> > sensors...
>
>Diesel fuel is often VERY high in sulfur, so there is some risk of harming 
>these components.  More assuredly though, diesel fuel is REALLY low in 
>octane rating. The whole point with diesel fuel is that you *want* it to 
>autoignite.  I'm not sure why you would want to add it to gasoline (what 
>sort of 'treatment' are you hoping to replace?), but if your goal is to 
>get it to knock like a woodpecker and run on incessantly, it's a good 
>place to start.
>
>SOunds like a bad idea....






